  "title": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Autoimmune myopathy"
  },
  "definition": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Autoimmune myopathy is a subgroup of idiopathic inflammatory myopathies, which, despite diverse causes, have the common histopathological features of myocyte necrosis without significant inflammation. Patients present with a subacute severe symmetrical proximal myopathy, associated with a markedly elevated creatine kinase level. These are most likely immune-mediated, as they respond to immunotherapy. It is often accompanied by statin therapy, connective tissue diseases, cancer, and autoantibodies specific for signal recognition particle (SRP) or 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutarylâ€“coenzyme A reductase (HMGCR)."
  },
